Design is the method of putting form and content together. Design, just as art, has multiple definitions; there is no single definition. Design can be art. Design can be aesthetics.
Engineering, architecture and painting are concerned not with the necessary but with the contingent - not with how things are but with how they might be.
What is design? It's where you stand with a foot in two worlds - the world of technology and the world of people and human purposes - and you try to bring the two together.
I'm not like most designers, who have to set sail on an exotic getaway to get inspired. It's on my walk to work, or in the subway and seeing something out of context.
All conventional wisdom has an element of truth to it, but good design requires more than an element of truth - it requires correct assumptions and valid calculations.
To whom does design address itself: to the greatest number, to the specialist of an enlightened matter, to a privileged social class? Design addresses itself to the need.
